# ss_birthdeath.net — GH #12 open-system steady-state output-sensitivity fixture.
#
# Birth-death: dS/dt = k_prod - k_deg·S  ⇒  S* = k_prod/k_deg = 2.5.
# No conservation law, so the steady-state solver takes the FULL-space
# sensitivity path (complementing the reduced-space path in ss_output_sens.net):
#   dS*/dk_prod = 1/k_deg,   dS*/dk_deg = -k_prod/k_deg².
# Observable Stot = S; function sq() = scale·Stot references the observable and
# the function-only parameter `scale` (explicit ∂sq/∂scale = Stot).
begin parameters
    1 k_prod 5.0
    2 k_deg  2.0
    3 scale  3.0
end parameters
begin species
    1 S() 0.0
end species
begin reactions
    1 0 1 k_prod   #_source
    2 1 0 k_deg    #_sink
end reactions
begin groups
    1 Stot 1
end groups
begin functions
    1 sq() scale*Stot
end functions
